Definition: You will be shown text describing {Biological Summary}. Your job is to determine the proteins that are {Relationship Summary} described. {Task-Specific Relationship}
Biological Summary: a cellular component, or a location relative to cellular structures in which proteins perform functions, either a cellular compartment (e.g., mitochondrion), or a stable macromolecular complex of which they are parts (e.g., the ribosome)
Task-Specific Relationship: Involvement is determined by whether or not there is evidence from an experiment directly supporting the annotation of the protein.
